summary: YWHAH, encoded by gene ENSG00000128245 on chromosome 22, codes for the 14-3-3 eta protein, involved in diverse signaling pathways. It functions as an adapter protein, binding to phosphoserine- or phosphothreonine-containing proteins.

ENSG00000166913 (YWHAB) encodes a protein kinase C inhibitor involved in signal transduction and regulation. It is located on chromosome 20 and has multiple aliases, including 14-3-3 protein beta/alpha.

YWHAE (ENSG00000108953) encodes the 14-3-3 epsilon protein, involved in signal transduction and regulation of various cellular processes. It functions as a protein kinase C inhibitor and interacts with numerous proteins, participating in cell cycle control, apoptosis, and stress response pathways.

YWHAG (ENSG00000170027) encodes the 14-3-3 gamma protein, involved in various signaling pathways by binding to phosphoserine-containing proteins. Mutations in this gene are associated with developmental and epileptic encephalopathy 56 (DEE56).

Gene ENSG00000134308 (YWHAQ) encodes the 14-3-3 theta protein, a key regulator involved in various cellular processes via protein-protein interactions. It is located on chromosome 2 and is associated with the HGNC ID 12854.
SFN (ENSG00000175793) encodes stratifin, a 14-3-3 protein sigma involved in cell cycle regulation and epithelial cell function, located on chromosome 1 between 26863149 and 26864456.
